{
    "id": "296",
    "title": "IMPROVE Bleeding Risk Score",
    "desc": "The IMPROVE Bleeding Risk Score evaluates bleeding risk at hospital admission.",
    "data": {
        "orgreference": [
            {
                "href": "https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20453069/",
                "text": "Decousus H, Tapson VF, Bergmann JF, et al. Factors at admission associated with bleeding risk in medical patients: findings from the IMPROVE investigators. Chest. 2011;139(1):69-79."
            }
        ],
        "other_refer": [],
        "evidence": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>The IMPROVE Bleeding Risk Score is calculated by the addition of the selected points:</span><b></b></p>\n<div dir=\"ltr\" align=\"left\">\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 46.2963%;\"><col style=\"width: 31.034%;\"><col style=\"width: 22.6697%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Variable</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Points</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"3\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Age, years</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>&lt;40</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>40-84</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>1.5</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>&ge;85</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>3.5</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Gender</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Female</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Male</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>1</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"3\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Renal function (<abbr title=\"Glomerular filtration rate\">GFR</abbr>), mL/min/m</span><sup><span>2</span></sup></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>&ge;60</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>30-59</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>1</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>&lt;30</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>2.5</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Current cancer (evidence of active malignancy within the last 6 months)</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>No</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Yes</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>2</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Rheumatic disease</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>No</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Yes</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>2</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Central venous catheter</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>No</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Yes</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>2</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>ICU/<abbr title=\"Coronary care unit\">CCU</abbr></span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>No</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Yes</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>2.5</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Evidence of hepatic failure (<abbr title=\"International normalized ratio\">INR</abbr> &gt;1.5)</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>No</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Yes</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>2.5</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Platelet count, cells/L</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>&ge;50 x 10</span><sup><span>9</span></sup></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>&lt;50 x 10</span><sup><span>9</span></sup></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>4</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Bleeding in 3 months before admission</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>No</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Yes</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>4</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Active gastroduodenal ulcer</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>No</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>0</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Yes</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>4.5</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p></p>",
        "facts": "<div dir=\"ltr\" align=\"left\">\n<table><colgroup><col><col></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>IMPROVE Score</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Risk of Bleeding</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>&lt;7</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>No increased risk of bleeding</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>&ge;7</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Increased risk of bleeding</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Major bleeding:</strong><span> A bleeding event contributing to death, bleeding associated with a &ge;2 g/dL fall in Hg, or leading to transfusion of &ge;2 units of packed red blood cells, or within a critical organ (including intracranial, retroperitoneal, intraocular, adrenal gland, spinal, or pericardial bleeding).</span></li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><span><strong>Non-major but clinically relevant bleeding:</strong> Overt gastrointestinal bleeding (except for insignificant hemorrhoidal bleeding), gross hematuria (macroscopic and lasting longer than 24 hours), substantial epistaxis that requires intervention and is recurrent and/or lasts &ge;5 minutes, extensive hematoma or bruising (&gt;5 cm in diameter), intra-articular bleeding (documented by aspiration), menorrhagia or metrorrhagia (increased quantity or duration), other bleeding important enough to be recorded on the hospital chart.</span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>",
        "estimation": [],
        "primary_complains": [
            "Bleeding",
